claim.claim-text:
14. A method for operating a first access point, the method comprising:
receiving, at the first access point, power from a power supply of a host device via a first connector that removably connects with a second connector associated with the host device, wherein the host device includes a first processing unit powered by the power supply;
directly powering a second processing unit of the first access point with the power received via the first connector, wherein the second processing unit is separate from the first processing unit;
establishing (i) a first wireless connection with a first station and (ii) a second wireless connection with a second station via a wireless communication module of the first access point;
forming a first basic service set (BSS) including the first access point, the first station, and the second station;
receiving, with the wireless communication module of the first access point, a first data unit from the first station, wherein the first data unit is addressed to the second station;
transmitting, with the communication module of the first access point, the first data unit to the second station without transmitting the first data unit to the host device via the first connectors;
establishing a third wireless connection with a second access point via the wireless communication module of the first access point; and
causing the first access point to join a second BSS as a station, wherein the second BSS includes the first access point and the second access point.
